"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/978-0-253-20810-1\" title=\"Special:BookSources/978-0-253-20810-1\">978-0-253-20810-1</a> \u2013 page 41 on discovery of deficiency diseases</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-4\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-4\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=K2V7qt0YFaIC&amp;pg=PA214&amp;dq=hu+ssu-hui&amp;as_brr=3&amp;hl=ru&amp;sig=ACfU3U1fo6yNjd2hfgdBPwPrYCsg2R_ROg\"><b>Unschuld, Paul Ulrich. Medicine in China: A History of Pharmaceutics.</b></a><b> University of California Press, 1986. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-520-05025-8\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-520-05025-8\">0-520-05025-8</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780520050259\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780520050259\">9780520050259</a></b> pages 213\u2014214</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-5\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-5\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Allsen, Thomas T. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://books.google.com/books?id=0StLNcKQNUoC&amp;pg=PA131&amp;dq=hu+ssu-hui&amp;as_brr=3&amp;hl=ru&amp;sig=ACfU3U3aKGI6m82_cQ1FsFIPKRFAY10Bnw#PPA131,M1\">Culture and Conquest in Mongol Eurasia.</a> Cambridge University Press, 2001. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0-521-60270-X\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0-521-60270-X\">0-521-60270-X</a>, 9780521602709 \u0441\u0442\u0440. 130\u2014131</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-6\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-6\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Husihui, Paul D. Buell,  Eugene N. Anderson, tr., <i>A Soup for the Qan: Chinese Dietary Medicine of the Mongol Era as Seen in Hu Szu-Hui's Yin-Shan Cheng-Yao: Introduction, Translation, Commentary and Chinese Text</i>  (London; New York: Kegan Paul International,  2000. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0710305834\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0710305834\">0710305834</a>), p. 169.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-7\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-7\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\">Hu Sihui, <i>A Soup for the Qan</i> p 295.</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-8\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-8\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://china.org.cn/english/imperial/26109.htm\">Imperial Food in the Ming Dynasty</a> \u043d\u0430 \u0441\u0430\u0439\u0442\u0435 China Internet Information Center</span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-9\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-9\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><cite class=\"citation web\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://english.hanban.edu.cn/english/features/beijing/31300.htm\">\"Beijing Duck\"</a>. <i>International Chinese Language Council website</i>. China Internet Information Center. 2008<span class=\"reference-accessdate\">. Retrieved <span class=\"nowrap\">2008-10-17</span></span>.</cite><span title=\"ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=International+Chinese+Language+Council+website&amp;rft.atitle=Beijing+Duck&amp;rft.date=2008&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fenglish.hanban.edu.cn%2Fenglish%2Ffeatures%2Fbeijing%2F31300.htm&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AHu+Sihui\" class=\"Z3988\"><span style=\"display